## Executive Overview

The BOEING 220-Y HYBRID SUPERCRUISE program represents the second-generation aerospace integration platform within the PI220 aerospace lineage.

Where the Boeing 220-X focused on proving that multiple advanced systems could operate together, the Boeing 220-Y focused on optimizing those systems for sustained high-efficiency flight.

The program introduced:

* Expanded AFAT integration
* Advanced X2M predictive governance
* Hybrid propulsion management
* Enhanced STARFRAME deployment
* Long-range endurance methodologies
* Early distributed-flight intelligence concepts

The Boeing 220-Y became the direct technological predecessor to the Boeing 220-G family and served as the first platform to demonstrate the principles that would later mature into distributed aerospace intelligence.

